xt(a) = b\) . \(N\) is called connected, if all nodes in \(N\) are equivalent under \(\lr\) . The connected components of \(N\) are the elements in \(N/\lr\) . Proposition. If \(N\) is finite, then \(a \lr b\) if and only if \(T(a) = T(b)\) . Proof. The condition \(T(a) = T(b)\) clearly defines an equivalence relation. We have to show that every other equivalence relation \(\approx\) that extends \(a a b\) also extends \(T(a) = T(b)\) . For \(a,b \in N\) with \(T(a) = T(b)\) , we have \(a \approx t\) for all \(t \in T(a)\) since \(T(a) \subset P(a)\) . Since \(T(a)=T(b)\) is non-empty we find \(t \in T(a) = T(b)\) , and \(a \approx t \approx b\) , hence \(a \approx b\) . qed. Sub-Structures Definition. A sub-structure of a Linked Structure \(N\) is a subset \(A \subset N\) , so that \(
